http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Traffic-curbs-in-city-today/article13995110.ece

Traffic restrictions will be in place in the city from 11.30 a.m. on Tuesday in connection with the visit of Vice President Hamid Ansari to the State capital. According to the City Police, restrictions will be in place in two sessions, from 11.30 a.m. to 1.30 p.m. on the Shanghumughom–Raj Bhavan route and from 3.15 p.m. to 6.30 p.m. on the VellayambalamPMG route. Diversions, parking regulations and movement restrictions would be enforced on the route starting from Shanghumughom and via All Saints–Chakka–Pettah–Pattoor–General Hospital Junction–Asan Square–Palayam–RR Lamp–Museum– Vellayambalam–Raj Bhavan.In the afternoon, from 3.15 p.m., similar enforcements would be in place along Vellayambalam, Vazhuthacaud, Museum, RR Lamp, World War Memorial, Palayam and PMG. Asking air passengers to reach the airport in advance to avoid missing their flights, the police have asked the public to call on 1099, 94979 87001, 94979 87002, 0471-2558731 and 0471-2558732 to lodge complaints or suggestions with regard to traffic.